  m_Name: DialogNPCInfirmary
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Name: Stefano
  Icon: {fileID: -2105629146, guid: d556a7f542c7d03429c5a535ce31a084, type: 3}
  HasInteraction: 0
  interactionType: 1
  Greeting: Hey...
  Day1Dialog:
  - "Welcome, boy. I keep the fort standing \u2014 walls, gates, supplies. The Ottomans
    land on the northern shore, but the fort was built on rock, so they cannot tunnel
    under it. Every plank and barrel could mean life or death."
  Day2FirstTimeDialog:
  - Cannonballs tear at the northern walls; the enemy digs trenches, but the rock
    beneath prevents tunneling. Food and water must be rationed carefully. Every
    action buys hours, maybe lives.
  Day2MetBeforeDialog:
  - Yesterday you saw repairs; today, gates creak and walls shudder under fire. Even
    small reinforcements may hold the enemy at bay. Men cling to life as the fort
    groans under bombardment.
  Day3FirstTimeDialog:
  - The enemy trenches cut closer to the northern bastions, but they cannot undermine
    the foundations. Every barrel of supplies, every reinforced gate is a lifeline.
    Death is near, courage alone cannot save the fort.
  Day3MetBeforeDialog:
  - Yesterday, basic repairs; today, debris blocks paths, men are exhausted. Every
    plank hammered delays disaster, but the enemy grows stronger.
  Day4FirstTimeDialog:
  - Water runs low, stores dwindle, morale falters. Every nail, ration, plank may
    save a life. The fort survives on grit and desperation, protected by the rock
    foundations.
  Day4MetBeforeDialog:
  - You return. Yesterday, stores; today, walls and gates strain under bombardment.
    Each repair prolongs life, but many fall outside. Survival is grim and fleeting.
  Day5FirstTimeDialog:
  - Tomorrow may be the bloodiest day. Every repair, ration, and plank is survival
    against overwhelming odds. The fort will be tested like never before, but its
    foundations hold firm.
  Day5MetBeforeDialog:
  - "This is it. Every repair, ration, reinforced gate may decide who lives. The
    fort may hold, but suffering is immense. Courage here comes at a terrible price
    \u2014 remember that, boy."
  dayNumber: 1
  metOnday1: 0
  metOnday2: 0
